nonlinear systems under data-rate constraints, which holds for
trajectories confined within a known bounded region of the state
space. To render the region actually invariant, the data rate must
be suitably chosen. The data rate needed to achieve the
stabilization goal is shown to depend on the size of the set of
initial conditions only.
