The problem of fault detection for linear continuous-time systems via encoded
information
is considered. The encoded information is received at a remote
location by
the monitoring device and assessed to infer the occurrence of the fault. A
class of faults is considered which allows to use a
simple decision logic as monitoring device.
<p>
<li>
<SPAN
