Proc. of <em>42nd IEEE Conf. Dec. Contr.</em>, CDC03,  Maui, HI. </span><br>
The problem of asymptotic stabilization under input
constraints in the case in which feedback information is sent through a
communication channel is studied. The process to control is
comprised of a chain of integrators cascaded to a zero dynamics. A
solution is given which provides encoder, decoder and controller
accomplishing asymptotic stabilization of the closed-loop system
while fulfilling the constraints. The communication channel
has finite bandwidth, transmission delay and
adaptive transmission rate.
The result is given for a variety of cases which include
state and output feedback,
ISS and integral ISS zero dynamics.
The number of bits used to encode the
information generated by the process and which is needed to the purpose
of stabilizing the process is explicitly assessed.
