fundamental importance in modern infrastructures. Many of these
large-scale systems are complex interconnections of sub-components
which interact by means of communication channel with limited
bandwidth. Therefore the information must be encoded in order to
be transmitted. Given a class of encoders, we study the problem of
detecting faults affecting some of these  sub-components starting
from the encoded information, and precisely characterize a class
of faults which can be detected.
