The recently introduced geometric approach to the nonlinear fault detection and
isolation problem is used in this paper to detect actuator faults
for the vertical takeoff and landing aircraft. The approach leads to
a filter which, by processing the outputs of the plant, detects the
faults and distinguishes which one is occurring.
